The symmetric difference `symmDiff M P` is the set of edges that are in `M` or in `P` but not in both. This is equivalent to `(M \ P) ∪ (P \ M)`.

We can use the formula for the cardinality of a symmetric difference:
`|A Δ B| = |A| + |B| - 2|A ∩ B|`.

In our case, `A = M` and `B = P`. So we have:
